- a. Use weight shift to turn
- b. Weight shift and add brake input in the direction you want to turn while keeping some pressure in the opposite brake
- c. Pull down on the brake in the direction you want to turn
- d. Pull down on the brake in the direction you want to turn and let the other hand up at the same time

